---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Guide to Order Status Pages - parcelLab"
  description="An order status page is a self-service portal where shoppers track their orders. Learn how to optimize it for better retention, engagement, and fewer WISMO inquiries."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Post-Purchase</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">Guide to Order Status Pages</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Julian Krenge</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2023-08-28">August 28, 2023</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>7 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          With rising customer acquisition costs, supply chain complexity, and changing consumer habits, a generic post-purchase experience is no longer enough. One of the ways to take your post-purchase experience to the next level is to have an order status page hosted on your website -- a self-service portal where ecommerce shoppers can track the progress of their order from processing through shipping and delivery.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Optimize Your Order Status Page</h2>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)] mt-8 mb-3">Provide Everything Customers Need in One Place</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Your brand's page should include:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Production and warehouse updates</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Delivery tracking</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Details on multipackage orders</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Inflight options for address or schedule changes</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Feedback options</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#035740" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Personalized recommendations</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)] mt-8 mb-3">Build a Community and Create Customer Excitement</h3>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          An order-tracking page is a great way to promote your customer community and differentiate your brand. Share posts from your Instagram, customers, and influencers to create an emotional connection. Ask customers to promote their purchase on social media once they receive it. Add links for customers to opt into SMS notifications or sign up for newsletters and special events.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Your post-purchase platform should integrate with your recommendation engine to encourage customers to shop while they wait, and suggest accessories and related products for follow-on purchases. Your brand can also use this page to support integrated marketing campaigns with ad space for upsell engagement.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">Key Benefits</h2>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Increase Customer Retention</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Staying connected post-purchase is extremely important for retention. Sending automatic updates is a great way to keep customers happy and excited about their order.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Reduce WISMO Inquiries</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Customers have instant access to any information regarding their order, so they won't feel the need to contact customer service agents. A personalized order status page is known to reduce customer inquiries by up to 25%.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Improve Customer Engagement</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Encouraging customers to interact with social media pages and leave feedback shows you care and keeps customers engaged. When you add targeted content to the order tracking page, your brand can improve open and click-through rates because customers see relevant content while most engaged.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed mt-8">
          While waiting for their package, customers often check the order status page several times. Since this page is hosted on your brand's website, you can view analytics to see how changes impact site traffic and adjust for better results. It's also best practice to link to an FAQ page or a preferred channel for inquiries, managing queries in a cost-effective way.
        </p>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Since it requires a lot of time, money, and effort to gain a customer, it is necessary for brands to implement tracking pages that will convert, build loyalty, and increase engagement. That's why more than 800 retailers have chosen parcelLab as their post-purchase experience platform.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
